================================================================================
JBox2D
================================================================================

The package com.codename1.gaming.physics.box2d is a derived work of JBox2D
(https://github.com/jbox2d/jbox2d), a Java port of Erin Catto's Box2D physics
engine. The sources have been repackaged from org.jbox2d into
com.codename1.gaming.physics.box2d and lightly adapted for the Codename One
virtual machines, with no algorithmic changes. The adaptations are mechanical
and reproducible, so the engine can be re-vendored from a newer JBox2D release:

  * StrictMath is replaced with Math and GWT specific emulation removed.
  * The unused java.io.Serializable markers (and serialVersionUID fields) are
    stripped from the math classes -- Codename One apps do not serialize them.
  * The internal profiling Timer helper, which duplicated functionality the
    platform already provides, is removed and inlined to direct
    System.currentTimeMillis() arithmetic at its call sites.

The original copyright and license notices are retained in each source file.

